|GKB-- Rituals ----------------------------------------------------|000

Druid rituals are prepared workings that shape your nwyfre before
or between fights.  They may restore vessels, expand capacity, or
improve regeneration for a time.  Later rites can also conserve
nwyfre, convert one current into another, or bind short-lived
companions and spirits.

Some newer rites are long-running rituals.  These toggle on and off,
stay with you while you travel, and react to movement or other future
events instead of ending after a fixed timer.

Learn rituals in the Druid Grove inside the guild hall:

  |CKBlearn ritual <name>|000

Use these commands to inspect them:

  |CKBritual               |000 Show your current rite and active effects.
  |CKBritual list          |000 List rituals you know.
  |CKBritual stop <name>   |000 End a long-running ritual.
  |CKBnwyfre rituals        |000 List rituals you know.
  |CKBnwyfre learnable      |000 List rituals you can learn.
  |CKBnwyfre ritual <name>  |000 Show requirements and effect.

Ritual material costs come from the profession material stores shown
by |CKBreagents|000.  Use |CKBreagents search <item>|000 to check an
exact herb, creature reagent, skin, ore, bolt, or special shard.

Perform a ritual with:

  |CKBritual <name>|000

Some rituals require an argument:

  |CKBritual drawing of the tide tellurian|000
  |CKBritual lunar draught marken|000
  |CKBritual vessel expansion daloan|000

Current-based rituals show the exact profession materials for each
current in |CKBnwyfre ritual <name>|000.

Conversion rituals require two currents:

  |CKBritual tide exchange tellurian daloan|000
  |CKBritual equinox channel daloan marken|000

When all three moons are new, the lunar currents are all weak at once:

  |CKBritual moonless drawing|000

This rite uses common Daloan, Marken, and Tekali herbs to restore part
of each lunar vessel without needing lunar nwyfre first.

Some rituals may leave you with a companion or tool:

  |CKBraven pact    |000 Adds |CKBraven scout|000 for nearby paths.
  |CKBhearth spirit |000 Adds a quiet healing spirit for a short time.

Long-running rituals remain active until you end them:

  |CKBverdant refrain|000 Quietly hum and sing while traveling, sometimes
                     gathering profession herbs and saved reagents in
                     natural places.

For the Druid menagerie and its companion-summoning rites, use
|CKBdhelp companions|000.

Conjunction rituals are rarer.  They only work when the sky agrees:

  |CKBtwin-moon pact             |000 Needs two full moons at night.
  |CKBtriple confluence calling  |000 Needs all three full moons and
                                 an ancient Sacred Grove.

Most prepared rituals require you to stand still until the rite
completes.  Moving or entering combat breaks the pattern.  Long-running
rituals are different: they are toggles, and their active effects
simply pause when conditions are wrong.

New druids should start with:

  |CKBlearn ritual drawing of the tide|000
  |CKBritual drawing of the tide marken|000

Use |CKBdhelp beginner|000 for the full first-hour path.
